The logic here looks reversed from what the text specifies. It is specified as (pseudocode):

```
// apply powerSupply increment always
...

if ( powerSupply != kPowerSupplyExternalUnstable && powerSupply != kPowerSupplyBattery ) { 
          weight += kIsUnstableInc
}
```

So then a device that is externally powered with UPS-backup, but due to some other bug/issue reboots very often, would have weighting 64 + 4 - 4 = 64.

And a battery-powered device (normally weight 56) that due to some bug/issue reboots very often, would remain at weight 56.   (Current code will cause weight 60 to be used, too high.)

